cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with image classification using deep neural networks, specifically convolutional autoencoders and convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training and optimization of neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of autoencoders for feature extraction and initialization of a supervised network suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks for classification also suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with paintings as the dataset, which suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
